This paper focuses on the use of deep generative models for the generation of inorganic chemical compositions. The paper discusses the use of conditional VAEs and GANs, which are commonly studied in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of physical descriptors, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) applications. Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the effectiveness of the generative models, which falls under the category of statistical learning (cs.SD). Finally, the paper mentions the use of Metropolis-Hastings-based atomic valency modification, which is a technique commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL).
